Project Overview
This project showcases a full-cycle analysis of an e-commerce dataset (Brazilian E-Commerce Public Dataset by Olist from Kaggle). 
It covers data cleaning, exploration, sales and customer segmentation analysis, visualization, and actionable business insights,
culminating in an interactive Power BI dashboard.

1. Data Cleaning & Exploration

The first step focused on understanding the dataset and preparing it for analysis.
Key Steps Performed in Python (Jupyter Notebook / VS Code):
Handled missing and duplicate values in all tables (orders, customers, items, products, payments, reviews, sellers, geo).
Standardized column names and data types, especially for timestamps and numeric fields.
Filled missing values with medians, zero, or default strings as appropriate.
Explored basic trends, distributions, and dataset statistics to understand sales, product, and customer patterns.

Files & References:

