2. Customer & Payment Analysis

After cleaning the dataset, I performed detailed business analysis focusing on orders, payments, and customer behavior.
Analysis Performed:
Calculated Total Sales and Total Payments using DAX in Power BI measures.
Segmented orders by status (delivered, canceled, processing) and visualized proportions.
Explored payment types (credit card, boleto, voucher) and their distribution using Pie Charts.
Generated KPI cards for key metrics: Total Sales, Total Payments, Total Orders.

Files & References:
ðŸ“‚ Notebook: 04_Sales_Analysis.ipynb â€“ Python code and Power BI measures for sales KPIs
ðŸ“‚ Power BI Dashboard: PowerBI_Dashboard/ â€“ screenshots of KPIs and visuals

Product Performance & Top Categories

Next, I focused on analyzing products and categories to find the best-performing items.
Analysis Performed:
Computed Total Payment per Product Category.
Created Top 10 Product Categories by Revenue bar chart using Power BI.
Visualized product distribution and sales trends across categories and time.
Identified key product categories driving the majority of revenue.

Files & References:
ðŸ“‚ Notebook: 05_Product_Analysis.ipynb
ðŸ“‚ Dashboard Visuals: Include bar charts, stacked charts, and filters for top products

4. Geographic Insights
To understand regional patterns:
Mapped customer and seller geolocations using Power BI map visuals.
Analyzed distribution of orders and sales across cities and states.
Identified regions with higher sales volume or delivery delays for business decisions.

Files & References:
ðŸ“‚ Notebook: 06_Geo_Analysis.ipynb
ðŸ“‚ Power BI Map Visuals: screenshots of geographic distributions


Finally, I built a Power BI Dashboard to present all insights in an interactive, business-friendly format.
Dashboard Pages & Highlights:
Home / Overview: Quick KPI cards, slicers for filtering by date, payment type, or order status
Sales Performance: Total Sales, Total Payments, Total Orders with trend line charts
Product Insights: Top categories, product-level revenue breakdown
Customer Insights: Order segmentation, payment preferences, loyalty indicators
Geographic Insights: Maps showing order distribution and sales hotspots
Executive Summary: Key metrics and insights for business decision-making

